songs.title: Blame Joy
songs.lyrics:
[Intro]
Oh-oh, oh-oh, oh-oh

[Verse 1]
First time I met her, we were kids
Her dark side was getting [on her lips?]
We snuck out, stole my parents' car
Crashed in my neighbor's yard, didn't get very far

[Chorus]
Blame Joy, she messed me up
And then she showed me things a girl should never see
Blame Joy, she messed me up
And then she showed me things a girl should never see

[Verse 2]
[?], oh, [?]
[?] you got me [?]
[?]
I get [?]

[Chorus]
Blame Joy, she messed me up
And then she showed me things a girl should never see
Blame Joy, she messed me up
And then she showed me things a girl should never see

[Outro]
Oh-oh, oh-oh, oh-oh
